{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":20198,"record_hash":"sha256:b207d4423a4d2089af05a15905c53c717b1dc199e956bebc3ed0c46c74338d8a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T11:31:01.404Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes. I think the cleanest formulation is:\n\n`AgentSession` should not be the in-memory type here.\n\nThe durable thing in GitMeta is the **agent session**. But the Rust value we build during one command invocation is not the session itself. It is an incoming transcript payload that should be merged into that durable session.\n\nI’d name it something like:\n\n```rust\nTranscriptImport\n```\n\nor slightly more explicit:\n\n```rust\nSessionTranscriptImport\n```\n\nMy preference is `TranscriptImport`: short, concrete, and it avoids implying that each capture creates a new session.\n\nThe shape would read like this:\n\n```rust\nParsedTranscript\n    -> TranscriptImport\n    -> merge_transcript_import(...)\n    -> GitMeta durable session keys\n```\n\nWhere:\n\n```rust\nstruct TranscriptImport {\n    session_key: String,\n    source_key: String,\n    source: TranscriptSource,\n    records: Vec<TranscriptRecord>,\n}\n```\n\nAnd then:\n\n```rust\nstruct TranscriptSource {\n    agent: String,\n    provider: Option<String>,\n    model: Option<String>,\n    tool_version: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\nThe write function should probably not be `write_session`, because that also sounds like “create or overwrite the session.” Better names:\n\n```rust\nmerge_transcript_import(...)\n```\n\nor:\n\n```rust\nwrite_transcript_import(...)\n```\n\nI slightly prefer `merge_transcript_import` because the dedupe behavior is the whole point: repeated captures/imports for the same durable session append only unseen records.\n\nSo the concepts become:\n\n- `ParsedTranscript`: what we got from parsing an agent transcript file.\n- `TranscriptImport`: the record-shaped payload prepared for GitMeta.\n- `TranscriptSource`: metadata about the transcript source/provider.\n- `TranscriptRecord`: one stored redacted transcript entry.\n- `AgentSessionKeys`: key builder for the durable GitMeta agent session.\n- `merge_transcript_import`: merges this import into the durable GitMeta session.\n\nThat preserves the important mental model: capture is just how data enters the system; GitMeta stores durable sessions plus append-only transcript records.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T11:31:01.404Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}